#Pulling in the metadata for the remainder of the analysis
metadata <- read_csv("/Users/vupadhyay/Documents/Work/UCSF/TurnbaughLab/IDEO/RMDs_and_outputs/Data_Inputs/Metadata_RecodedWhite.csv")
## 
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),
##   SampleID = col_character(),
##   Gender = col_character(),
##   Ethnicity = col_character(),
##   IDEO_BMI_Class = col_character(),
##   MetSyn = col_character(),
##   Medication = col_character(),
##   Diabetes = col_character(),
##   Percent_BF_Class = col_character(),
##   HOMAIR_Class = col_character(),
##   Smoking = col_character(),
##   Drug_Use = col_character(),
##   USBorn = col_character(),
##   SFBorn = col_character(),
##   Education = col_character(),
##   Statin = col_character(),
##   Metformin = col_character()
## )
## ℹ Use `spec()` for the full column specifications.
metadata <- metadata[order(metadata$SampleID),]

metadata <- filter(metadata, Ethnicity=="White")
metadata <- filter(metadata,IDEO_BMI_Class=="Lean")
#Started With the ASA24 data import though we did not end up using this for the analysis
ASA24data <- readxl::read_xlsx("/Users/vupadhyay/Documents/Work/UCSF/TurnbaughLab/IDEO/RMDs_and_outputs/Data_Inputs/IDEO microbiome ASA24data May 2020VU.xlsx")
ASA24data <- ASA24data[order(ASA24data$SampleID),]

#Get rid of the excess ASA24 data
ASA24data <- filter(ASA24data, SampleID %in% metadata$SampleID)
#ASA24data <- slice(ASA24data,-2)

#Using DHQ3 data; of note, they provided two OB045 subjects in this DHQ3 data
DHQ3data <- read_csv("/Users/vupadhyay/Documents/Work/UCSF/TurnbaughLab/IDEO/RMDs_and_outputs/Data_Inputs/DHQ3 data not including HEI May 2020.csv")
## 
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),
##   SampleID = col_character()
## )
## ℹ Use `spec()` for the full column specifications.
DHQ3data <- DHQ3data[order(DHQ3data$SampleID),]
DHQ3data <- filter(DHQ3data, SampleID %in% metadata$SampleID)

#There are duplicates of OB045. In the metadata we're using, OB045 drinks 1.33 drinks per week, so I am deleting the row with OB045 that has no grams of alcohol per week. This is for the Ethnicity=="White" group
DHQ3data <- slice(DHQ3data,-3)

#Pull in the ASV data
SVtab<-read_qza("/Users/vupadhyay/Documents/Work/UCSF/TurnbaughLab/IDEO/RMDs_and_outputs/NewPipelineEval/DataInputs/ASV_table.qza")$data %>% as.data.frame() #SVtable.qza

#Filter out the V2s that are post-bariatric surgery
SVtab.subset <- select(SVtab, !c(grep(".V2", colnames(SVtab))))

#Rename the columns to match the IDEO metadata
colnames(SVtab.subset) <- gsub("*.V\\d", "", colnames(SVtab.subset))
#Rename the 0 with an O
colnames(SVtab.subset) <- gsub("0B", "OB", colnames(SVtab.subset))

#Filter out only the samples in IDEO
IDEOSVtab <- select(SVtab.subset, metadata$SampleID)
IDEOSVtab.filtered <- Confidence.Filter(IDEOSVtab, 3, 10, TRUE)
## Filtering features such that they are present in at least 3 samples with a total of at least 10 reads.
## ...There are 2708637 reads and 3607  features
## ...After filtering there are 2376294 reads and 515 features
IDEOSVtab.CZM <- zCompositions::cmultRepl(t(IDEOSVtab.filtered),
                                          label=0,
                                          method="CZM",
                                          output="p-counts",
                                          suppress.print = TRUE) %>%
  t()

IDEOSVtab.CLR <- apply(log2(IDEOSVtab.CZM), 2, function(x)x-mean(x))
DM <- daisy(t(IDEOSVtab.CLR), metric = c("euclidean")) %>% as.matrix()

SVseq<-read_qza("/Users/vupadhyay/Documents/Work/UCSF/TurnbaughLab/IDEO/RMDs_and_outputs/NewPipelineEval/DataInputs/ASV_sequences.qza")$data %>% as.data.frame() %>% rename(c("SV"="x")) #SVsequences.qza

taxonomy<-read_tsv("/Users/vupadhyay/Documents/Work/UCSF/TurnbaughLab/IDEO/RMDs_and_outputs/NewPipelineEval/DataInputs/ASV_d2taxonomy.txt") #SV_taxonomy_Dada2.txt
## 
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## cols(

lookup<-read_csv("/Users/vupadhyay/Documents/Work/UCSF/TurnbaughLab/IDEO/RMDs_and_outputs/NewPipelineEval/Outputs/ASVIDs.csv")
## 
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## 
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),

## ℹ Use `spec()` for the full column specifications.
metaphlan.strain = metaphlan[grep("t__",metaphlan$Taxonomy),]
metaphlan.species = metaphlan[grep("s__", metaphlan$Taxonomy),]%>% filter(!(Taxonomy %in% metaphlan.strain$Taxonomy)) %>% as.data.frame()

rownames(metaphlan.species) = metaphlan.species$Taxonomy
metaphlan.species$Taxonomy = NULL

metaphlan.species[is.na(metaphlan.species)] = 0
